title: Pa. Boys: Pa. boys: Ryan blanks Wood, 2-0
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Father Judge 2, Upper Dublin 1: Eddy Rangel and Eric Trush each scored, and the hosts, ranked No. 3 in Southeastern Pennsylvania by The Inquirer, improved to 13-0. Jose Balomeque scored for Upper Dublin.
North Penn 2, Holy Ghost Prep 1: The sixth-ranked visitors scored two first-half goals, including Michael Kohler's penalty kick. Owen Nakatami scored the other. Michael Varley scored for Holy Ghost Prep. 
PUBLIC LEAGUE 
Frankford 3, Martin Luther King 2: Nigel Johnson's goal from just inside the penalty area with 20 minutes left lifted the visitors. Amadou Kamagate scored twice. Runako Brown and Denisloni Pierre each tallied a goal for the hosts. 
Northeast 4, Franklin Towne Charter 1: Phedel Saye deposited two goals and Francisco Correia and Adin Hernandez scored a goal apiece for the visitors. Damian Schwiezer scored for Franklin Towne Charter. 
Science Leadership (Beeber) 5, Penn Treaty 0: Khafren Smith collected a hat trick and both Dashawn McIntosh-Innis and Wayne Stackhouse each added a goal for the hosts. Charles Riggs made three saves. 
Engineering & Science 5, Bartram 1: Ronald Magana netted two goals for the hosts. Matthew Bermeo, Jeff Cook, and Alexis Hernendez each scored one goal. 
Roxborough 8, Bodine 1: Aaron Summerville scored the first three goals of the game, and Matteo Tesei knocked in two more for the hosts. Xavier Fanny, John Laro, and Anthony Tarpeh each scored one goal. 
Boys' Latin 7, Edison 0: Jacquan Canty scored two goals and had one assist for the visitors. Jimmy Natee deposited two goals and had an assist. Isaiah Graham, Nate Robinson, Ayub Sayed, and Justin Walker had one goal apiece. 
Ches-Mont League 
Bishop Shanahan 1, West Chester East 0: With the game cut short at halftime due to inclement weather, Ricky Zink's first-half goal stood as the winner for the hosts. Pat Delaney had five saves. 
Friends Schools League 
Germantown Friends 2, Westtown 1: Freshman midfielder Sam Butler's goal - the first of his career - proved to be the winner when the contest was called at halftime due to weather. Isaac Myran had the assist.
